### Test: Create a simple user
POST https://localhost:7208/odata/Users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Enzo",
  "lastName": "Marquis"
}

###

### Get all users
GET https://localhost:7208/odata/Users
Accept: application/json

###

### Get user by ID (replace with actual GUID)
GET https://localhost:7208/odata/Users(00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000)
Accept: application/json

###

### Get user by email
GET https://localhost:7208/odata/Users/GetByEmail?email=john.doe@example.com
Accept: application/json

###

### Create a new user
POST https://localhost:7208/odata/Users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "dateOfBirth": "1990-05-15T00:00:00Z",
  "gender": "Male",
  "address": "123 Main Street",
  "city": "New York",
  "postalCode": "10001",
  "country": "United States"
}

###

### Update user (replace GUID with actual ID)
PUT https://localhost:7208/odata/Users(00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000)
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John Updated",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567899",
  "city": "Los Angeles"
}

###

### Delete user (replace GUID with actual ID)
DELETE https://localhost:7208/odata/Users(00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000)

###

### Get users with OData query options
GET https://localhost:7208/odata/Users?$filter=isActive eq true&$orderby=firstName&$top=10
Accept: application/json

###

### Get users by city
GET https://localhost:7208/odata/Users?$filter=city eq 'New York'
Accept: application/json